  "prompt": "Google Nexus 7: How to change default action for playing video from Engadget app? I have chosen YouTube but it doesn't play. My HTC One X uses streaming media player. How to change this default action to streaming media player?",
  "response": "To change the default video action on a Nexus 7, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. Go to Settings > Apps\n2. Find the Engadget app\n3. Tap on \"App details\"\n4. Look for \"Open by default\" or \"Default launch\" settings\n5. Check or modify the default video handler\n\nIf YouTube isn't working, you might want to:\n- Ensure YouTube app is updated\n- Check video playback settings in Engadget app\n- Try clearing app data/cache\n- Reinstall the Engadget app\n\nFor setting a specific media player as default:\n1. Go to Settings > Apps\n2. Tap the three-dot menu\n3. Select \"Default apps\"\n4. Look for \"Video viewer\" or similar option\n5. Choose your preferred media player\n\nFor HTC One X's streaming media player:\n- The exact method might differ depending on your Android version\n- You may need to set it as default in individual app settings\n- Some apps have their own video playback preferences\n\nIf these steps don't work, you might need to:\n- Check app-specific settings\n- Use a third-party app handler\n- Contact Engadget app support",
